data.title: Gannon finishes 7th nationally in D2 ADA Academic Achievement Award winners
data.meta_description: Gannon Athletics ranked seventh nationally with 209 student-athletes who claimed D2 ADA Academic Achievement Awards in 2023-24. Way to go, Golden Knights!
data.text:
Golden Knights lead PSAC with 209 D2 ADA honorees

CLEVELAND, Ohio – The Gannon University Athletic Department finished the 2023-24 academic/athletic year with 209 Division 2 Athletics Directors Association (D2 ADA) Academic Achievement Award winners among its student-athletes, the seventh-highest total in NCAA Division II.

The Academic Achievement Awards, in its 17th year, is a program that recognizes the academic accomplishments of student-athletes at the Division II level. The awards are presented to student-athletes who maintained a cumulative GPA of at least 3.50 on a 4.0 scale, completed at least two years of college-level work, and were active members of an NCAA team during the last academic year.

Gannon also led the Pennsylvania State Athletic Conference in D2 ADA Academic Achievement Award winners as the PSAC placed second among all Division II conferences with 1,919 honorees. The South Atlantic Conference led the nation with 2,076 winners.

Gannon trailed only Emmanuel (256), Lenoir-Rhyne (244), Florida Southern (230), Tiffin (228), Walsh (224), and Newberry (221) nationally in Division II.

The Golden Knights were part of a record-high 19,774 student-athletes from 192 institutions recognized for their academic achievements during the 2023-24 seasons. Since the inception of the award's program in 2007-08, there have been 167,396 student-athlete nominees recognized for their academic achievements at the Division II level.
